kjv_def: be able, avail, can do(-not), could, be good, might, prevail, be of strength, be whole, + much work
strongs_def: to have (or exercise) force (literally or figuratively)
outline:
1. to be strong
    1. to be strong in body, to be robust, to be in sound health
  2. to have power
    1. to have power as shown by extraordinary deeds
      1. to exert, wield power, to have strength to overcome
    2. to be a force, avail
    3. to be serviceable
    4. to be able, can
